      • TripPattern

        public TripPattern(TripPatternBase tripPatternBase,
           Trip trip,
           GtfsData gtfsData)
        Create a TripPattern. Note: The name comes from the trip trip_headsign data. If not set then uses name of last stop for trip.
        Parameters:
        tripPatternBase - Already have the TripPatternBase info so pass that in. That way it doesn't need to be recreated from Trip.
        trip - For supplying additional info
        gtfsData - So can access stop data for determining extent of trip pattern.

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        Description copied from class: TripPatternBase
        Needed so can have Set/Map of TripPatterns and looking up elements will be quick and proper. Note that this method does not do a full hashcode on paths. This is because the Path elements are not finalized when building up trip patterns. The tripPatternId still hasn't been set. So don't want to compare the entire Path objects. Instead, only use Path.basicHashCode(). This difference is very important so using an automatically generated method here would not suffice.
        Overrides:
        hashCode in class TripPatternBase

        Description copied from class: TripPatternBase
        Needed so can have Set/Map of TripPatterns and looking up elements will be quick and proper. Note that this method does not do a full equals() on paths. This is because the Path elements are not finalized when building up trip patterns. The tripPatternId still hasn't been set. So don't want to compare the entire Path objects. Instead, only use Path.basicEquals(). This difference is very important so using an automatically generated method here would not suffice.
